    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Heidelberg University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Early organ failure occurs frequently and is difficult to predict. The study aims to define a
      predictive score for early transplant failure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will be monitored 7 days following liver transplantation, including clinical scores,
      clinical chemistry, ultrasound findings and indocyaninegreen-clearance.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
